				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Why Burt Was Ousted</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-06-06T15:21:24+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">June 6, 2014 11:21 am</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">June 6, 2014 11:21 am</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/06/06/today-in-small-business-why-burt-was-ousted/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Why Burt Was Ousted" data-description="The economy regains the 8.7 million jobs lost in the recession. An owner gives away a coffee shop. And why the co-founder of Burt&#039;s Bees was ousted.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Employers <a href="//www.usatoday.com/story/money/business/2014/06/06/may-jobs-report/10037173/">added 217,000 jobs in May</a> as the labor market finally recovered all 8.7 million jobs lost in the recession.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Gallupâs <a href="//www.gallup.com/poll/170999/standard-living-index-climbs-six-year-high.aspx">standard of living index</a> climbs to six-year high and household net worth <a href="//www.chicagotribune.com/business/breaking/sns-rt-us-usa-fed-wealth-20140605,0,4339258.story">hits an</a> all-time record.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/boston/real_estate/2014/06/u-s-construction-spending-rebounded-in-april.html">Construction spending</a> rebounded in April but the outlook remains uncertain.</p>
